us.ihmc.euclid.geometry.interfaces

Interface Pose3DBasics

  • All Superinterfaces:
    us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.Clearable, Pose3DReadOnly, us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.Transformable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    FixedFramePose3DBasics, FramePose3DBasics
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FramePose3D, Pose3D

    public interface Pose3DBasics
extends Pose3DReadOnly, us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.Transformable, us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.Clearable
    Write and read interface for pose 3D.

    A pose 3D represents a position and orientation in 3 dimensions.

      • interpolate

        default void interpolate(Pose3DReadOnly other,
                         double alpha)
        Performs a linear interpolation from this to other given the percentage alpha.

        this.position = (1.0 - alpha) * this.position + alpha * other.position
        this.orientation = (1.0 - alpha) * this.orientation + alpha * other.orientation

        Parameters:
        other - the other pose 3D used for the interpolation. Not modified.
        alpha - the percentage used for the interpolation. A value of 0 will result in not modifying this, while a value of 1 is equivalent to setting this to other.

      • interpolate

        default void interpolate(Pose3DReadOnly pose1,
                         Pose3DReadOnly pose2,
                         double alpha)
        Performs a linear interpolation from pose1 to pose2 given the percentage alpha.

        this.position = (1.0 - alpha) * pose1.position + alpha * pose2.position
        this.orientation = (1.0 - alpha) * pose1.orientation + alpha * pose2.orientation

        Parameters:
        pose1 - the first pose 3D used in the interpolation. Not modified.
        pose2 - the second pose 3D used in the interpolation. Not modified.
        alpha - the percentage to use for the interpolation. A value of 0 will result in setting this to pose1, while a value of 1 is equivalent to setting this to pose2.

      • appendYawRotation

        default void appendYawRotation(double yaw)
        Appends a rotation about the z-axis to this pose 3D.

        More precisely, the position part is unchanged while the orientation part is updated as follows:

                                               / cos(yaw) -sin(yaw) 0 \
 this.orientation = this.orientation * | sin(yaw)  cos(yaw) 0 |
                                       \    0         0     1 /

        Parameters:
        yaw - the angle to rotate about the z-axis.

      • appendPitchRotation

        default void appendPitchRotation(double pitch)
        Appends a rotation about the y-axis to this pose 3D.

        More precisely, the position part is unchanged while the orientation part is updated as follows:

                                               /  cos(pitch) 0 sin(pitch) \
 this.orientation = this.orientation * |      0      1     0      |
                                       \ -sin(pitch) 0 cos(pitch) /

        Parameters:
        pitch - the angle to rotate about the y-axis.

      • appendRollRotation

        default void appendRollRotation(double roll)
        Appends a rotation about the x-axis to this pose 3D.

        More precisely, the position part is unchanged while the orientation part is updated as follows:

                                               / 1     0          0     \
 this.orientation = this.orientation * | 0 cos(roll) -sin(roll) |
                                       \ 0 sin(roll)  cos(roll) /

        Parameters:
        roll - the angle to rotate about the x-axis.
